[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m675[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m676[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m678[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m680[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:728[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m734[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m728[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT32[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, magic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* magic [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0xCACCACCA[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m729[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmagic != WF_MAGIC[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m730[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m731[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m[32m"invalid magic number [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m0x%08"[0m[39m PRIX32 [0m[32m""[0m[39m, magic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m732[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m733[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m734[0m[39m:    [0m[39m*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview and Root Cause Identification[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash in `rfx_process_message_metadata` is due to using a global pointer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`metadataBlock`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that is computed by adding an unvalidated offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`blockOffset`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom untrusted stream data. Subsequently, the code performs [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;` without any bounds checking, leading to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man out‐of‐bounds write when `blockOffset` is large or negative.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additionally, the guard in `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` checks for only [0m[1;36m8[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes remaining in the stream but reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtwo UINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, introducing a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotential over‐read and mis‐interpretation of stream data.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Fix Strategy[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Eliminate or Restrict Use of Global Mutable State[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace the globals `metadataBlock` and `metadataData` with local variables[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside the parsing context for each message. This ensures that one malformed frame [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcannot poison the next frame or other threads.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Store these as fields in the `RFX_CONTEXT` or the per‐message state object,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39me.g., `context->priv->metadataBlock` and `context->priv->metadataData`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Strengthen Stream Length Checks[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m671[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, change the guard to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure at least [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes are available before reading two UINT64 values:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or log an error and abort message processing[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This prevents partial reads and misaligned data causing insane offsets.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Validate `blockOffset` and `metadataBlock` Against a Known Valid Memory [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRegion[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Determine the intended valid range for metadata writes. Typically, metadata[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be written into a per‐message metadata buffer allocated by `rfx_context` at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mframe‐begin.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Introduce a new buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `UINT8* metadataBuffer` of known size [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataSize`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the context, allocated during `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprior to reading metadata parameters.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Instead of computing `metadataBlock = arbitrary_global + offset`, compute:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockOffset > metadataSize - [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m out‐of‐range offset[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         metadataBlockPtr = metadataBuffer + blockOffset;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Store `metadataBlockPtr` and `metadataData` in context locals for [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent `rfx_process_message_metadata`.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Safe Write in Metadata Handler[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `rfx_process_message_metadata`, replace the unguarded global write with:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         UINT8* ptr = context->priv->metadataBlockPtr;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m no valid metadata block[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mptr, &context->priv->metadataData, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This uses `memcpy` or direct assignment with guaranteed pointer within the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Step-by‐Step Implementation Plan[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `rfx.c`, define two new fields in the `RFX_PRIV` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor equivalent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m struct:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT8* metadataBuffer;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      size_t metadataSize;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT8* metadataBlockPtr;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT64 metadataData;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In `rfx_process_message_frame_begin`:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      a. Determine the maximum metadata size for this message [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbased on [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`numRegions` or protocol spec[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Allocate or resize `metadataBuffer` accordingly. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStore size in `metadataSize`.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      b. Replace the existing global‐state code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m680[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, context->priv->metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockOffset > context->priv->metadataSize - [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"metadata block offset out of range"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         context->priv->metadataBlockPtr = context->priv->metadataBuffer + [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblockOffset;[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      c. Remove or deprecate the file‐scope globals `metadataBlock` and [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataData`.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In `rfx_process_message_metadata`:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      a. After verifying the magic number, replace:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         with:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!context->priv->metadataBlockPtr[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->metadataBlockPtr, &context->priv->metadataData, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      b. Optionally zero out `metadataBlockPtr` after use to prevent reuse across [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessages.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Free or reuse `metadataBuffer` at the end of message processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_end`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensuring no memory leaks.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and Preservation of Logic[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By moving from globals to per‐message context state, we prevent cross‐message [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpollution and out‐of‐bounds writes due to unchecked offsets.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stronger stream length checks ensure that we do not read past the available [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput, thus avoiding misinterpretations.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validating `blockOffset` against a known buffer size directly enforces memory [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafety and closes the vulnerability.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using `memcpy` with a validated pointer preserves the intended functionality [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mstoring metadata data at the specified offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m without risking wild writes.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing protocol logic and message parsing remain intact; only the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal state management and safety checks are enhanced.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allocating a metadata buffer per message introduces some overhead; mitigate by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreusing a preallocated buffer when possible.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error paths now return FALSE early, ensuring that malformed metadata messages [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare simply rejected rather than processed.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing unit tests and fuzz harnesses should continue to operate, with the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdifference that out‐of‐range messages will be safely aborted rather than crashing. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEnsure backward compatibility by matching error codes.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References to Similar Code[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar safe‐buffer patterns exist elsewhere in `rfx.c` for tile data parsing,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere `tileData` buffers are allocated and bounds‐checked before writes. Mirror [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat approach for metadata.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>libfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:671[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>libfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:728[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m734[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mfreerdp[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp05dttj55[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTestFuzzCodecs -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arises when running the `TestFuzzCodecs` fuzzer against FreeRDP’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRFX codec: after a few iterations of clear codec errors, AddressSanitizer reports a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSEGV in rfx_process_message_metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild write to an invalid address via [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataBlock`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A patch attempt was made to disable metadata reads/writes by [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoving the global variables `metadataBlock` and `metadataData` and skipping over [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe metadata-handling code in `rfx.c`. However, the patch removed the variable [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations but left behind references to them, leading to compilation errors:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror: use of undeclared identifier [0m[32m'metadataBlock'[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror: use of undeclared identifier [0m[32m'metadataData'[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A libFuzzer run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCodecs`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers repeated clear-decompress errors [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand ultimately crashes in `rfx_process_message_metadata` with a write to an invalid[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddress.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - SEGV at `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrfx.[0m[1;92mc:734:26[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Caused by `*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;`[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Stack trace includes `rfx_process_message`, `TestFreeRDPCodecRemoteFX`, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe libFuzzer harness.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash indicates that `metadataBlock` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mused as a write pointer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperly initialized or validated before being dereferenced.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations and Findings[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m drives RFX codec decoding.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before the crash, multiple errors from `com.freerdp.codec.clear` appear, but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fatal error is in the RFX codec path.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code path in `rfx.c` reads a pair of [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit values from the stream [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`blockOffset`, `metadataData`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, updates `metadataBlock`, and then writes through [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat pointer.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Under malformed input, `metadataBlock` may point to arbitrary memory, leading [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto a wild write.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removed global declarations:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - UINT64 metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - UINT64 metadataData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the metadata-reading block to bail out if fewer than [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes remain, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsuming and ignoring the two [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit values:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return FALSE;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         UINT64 dummyOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, dummyData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, dummyOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, dummyData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ignoring metadataOffset and metadataData *[0m[35m/[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Commented out the write of `metadataData` to `metadataBlock`.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removed or disabled metadata-related writes around the magic-number check.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result and Compile Errors[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the patch, compilation fails because references to [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataBlock` and `metadataData` remain in the code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot fully removed or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarded[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, e.g.:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Errors point to lines [0m[1;36m735[0m[39m and subsequent lines in `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the write still exists, but the variables have been deleted.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Further Investigation[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review the definition and use of `metadataBlock` and `metadataData` in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx.c`, especially in:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `rfx_process_message_metadata` around line [0m[1;36m730[0m[39m.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Global variable declarations at the top of `rfx.c`.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine all code paths that read or write metadata to ensure consistency [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbetween declarations, reads, and writes.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Trace how `metadataBlock` is meant to be initialized and updated before any [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereference.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inspect related functions in the RFX codec [0m[1;39m([0m[32m"message metadata"[0m[39m handling[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproper boundary checks or conditional logic.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
